    "text": "Note that this workshops assumes a working knowledge of R; we will dive straight into main table content without a general overview of R.\n\n\nInstall and load packages\nThis workshop will use the packages tidyverse (for data manipulation and plotting), gtsummary (for table formatting) and medicaldata for example datasets.\n\nlibrary(tidyverse)\nlibrary(gtsummary)\nlibrary(medicaldata)\n\n\n\nExample data used\nThis session will use example datasets included in the gtsummary and medicaldata packages.\nLoad the [trial dataset] (https://www.danieldsjoberg.com/gtsummary/reference/trial.html?q=trial#ref-usage) and cytomegalovirus data\nA data frame with 200 rows–one row per patient\ntrt - Chemotherapy Treatment\nage - Age\nmarker - Marker Level (ng/mL)\nstage - T Stage\ngrade - Grade\nresponse - Tumor Response\ndeath - Patient Died\nttdeath - Months to Death/Censor\n\ntrial\n\n# A tibble: 200 × 8\n   trt      age marker stage grade response death ttdeath\n   &lt;chr&gt;  &lt;dbl&gt;  &lt;dbl&gt; &lt;fct&gt; &lt;fct&gt;    &lt;int&gt; &lt;int&gt;   &lt;dbl&gt;\n 1 Drug A    23  0.16  T1    II           0     0    24  \n 2 Drug B     9  1.11  T2    I            1     0    24  \n 3 Drug A    31  0.277 T1    II           0     0    24  \n 4 Drug A    NA  2.07  T3    III          1     1    17.6\n 5 Drug A    51  2.77  T4    III          1     1    16.4\n 6 Drug B    39  0.613 T4    I            0     1    15.6\n 7 Drug A    37  0.354 T1    II           0     0    24  \n 8 Drug A    32  1.74  T1    I            0     1    18.4\n 9 Drug A    31  0.144 T1    II           0     0    24  \n10 Drug B    34  0.205 T3    I            0     1    10.5\n# ℹ 190 more rows\n\n\n\ncytomegalovirus\n\n   ID age sex race                    diagnosis diagnosis.type\n1   1  61   1    0       acute myeloid leukemia              1\n2   2  62   1    1         non-Hodgkin lymphoma              0\n3   3  63   0    1         non-Hodgkin lymphoma              0\n4   4  33   0    1      